V{{For|the bailiff of Guernsey|Daniel de Lisle Brock}}\u000a'''Daniel''' ('''Dan''') '''W. Brock''' is an [[American philosopher]], [[bioethics|bioethicist]], and [[professor emeritus]].  He is the Frances Glessner Lee Professor Emeritus of [[Medical Ethics]] in the [http://ghsm.hms.harvard.edu Department of Global Health and Social Medicine] at [[Harvard Medical School]], the former Director of the [http://ghsm.hms.harvard.edu/research/medical_ethics/ Division of Medical Ethics] (now the Center for Bioethics) at the [[Harvard Medical School]], and former Director the [http://peh.harvard.edu/brock.html Director] of the [[Harvard University]] [http://PEH.Harvard.edu Program in Ethics and Health] (PEH).  He has held the Tillinghast Professorship at [[Brown University]] and served as a member of the Department of Clinical Bioethics at the [[National Institutes of Health]].<ref>http://www.bioethics.nih.gov/people/past_visiting.shtml</ref><ref>http://www.bioethics.nih.gov/about/</ref><ref>http://www.bioethics.nih.gov/about/blossoming.shtml</ref>  Brock earned his B.A. in economics from [[Cornell University]] and his Ph.D. in philosophy from [[Columbia University]].\u000a\u000aDan Brock has published over 150 articles relating to bioethics and philosophy and has served on numerous editorial boards.  He has also worked with various international organizations on bioethics as a consultant including the World Health Organization and has given papers and talks all over the world.\u000a\u000aHe was President of the American Association of Bioethics (AAB)<ref>http://www.asbh.org/about/archives/aab.html</ref><ref>http://www.lib.utexas.edu/taro/utmb/00004/utmb-00004.html</ref> in 1995-96, and was a founding Board Member of the [http://www.asbh.org American Society for Bioethics and Humanities].<ref>http://www.asbh.org</ref><ref>[http://www.asbh.org/about/history/ASBH_History.pdf ASBH History]</ref> He is a Fellow of the [[Hastings Center]], a bioethics research institution.\u000a\u000aDr. Brock is currently retired with his wife and spends his time between his Boston and New York residences.\u000a\u000a==HMS Center for Bioethics==\u000a* [http://medethics.med.harvard.edu/ HMS Center for Bioethics site], formerly the HMS Division of Medical Ethics (renamed July 1, 2014)\u000a* [http://medethics.med.harvard.edu/people/ Personnel]\u000a\u000a==Publications==\u000a* [http://connects.catalyst.harvard.edu/PROFILES/ProfileDetails.aspx?From=Pinfo&Person=DWB11 Dan Brock's Publications]\u000a* [https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Daniel+Brock%22&hl=en&btnG=Search Google Scholar search for Dan Brock: read portions of Dan Brock's writings]\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a<references/>\u000a\u000a==See also==\u000a* [[American philosophy]]\u000a* [[Health equity]]\u000a* [[List of American philosophers]]\u000a\u000a'''Collaborating Authors'''\u000a* [[Allen Buchanan]] of [http://www.Duke.edu Duke]\u000a* [[Norman Daniels]] of [http://www.HSPH.Harvard.edu HSPH]\u000a* [[Dan Wikler|Daniel Wikler]] of [http://www.HSPH.Harvard.edu HSPH]\u000a\u000a'''Institutions'''\u000a* [http://medethics.med.harvard.edu Harvard Medical Schools's DME]\u000a* [http://PEH.Harvard.edu Harvard University's PEH]\u000a* [[National Institutes of Health]]\u000a* [http://GHSM.HMS.Harvard.edu Harvard Medical Schools's Department of Global Health and Social Medicine]\u000a* [https://webapps.sph.harvard.edu/live/gremap/index_main.cfm?CFID=1000401&CFTOKEN=20018855 HSPH Research Ethics Map]\u000a\u000a'''News'''\u000a* [https://news.google.com/archivesearch?q=%22Daniel+Brock%22+source%3A%22-newswire%22+source%3A%22-wire%22+source%3A%22-presswire%22+source%3A%22-PR%22+source%3A%22-press%22+source%3A%22-release%22+ethics+Harvard&btnG=Search+Archives&scoring=a Google News Search for Dan Brock, Harvard Ethicist]\u000a* [http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&q=%22Daniel+Brock%22+-wikipedia+ethics+Harvard&btnG=Search&aq=f&oq=&aqi= Google Search for Dan Brock, Harvard Ethicist]\u000a\u000a{{A